Pre-Game Insights: South Korea head to China on the back of four straight wins with four goals or more and with five straight cleansheets.
Jurgen Klinsmann's men ran out 5-0 winners of Singapore to get their World Cup qualification campaign up and running.
China also picked up a win on Thursday, earning a 2-1 victory away to Thailand.
One alteration from the original squad named by Jurgen Klinsmann is that midfielder Hong Hyun-seok is out through injury with Jeonbuk's Park Jin-seob his replacement.
Beijing Guoan striker Zhang Yuning has been called into the squad despite only recently recovering from a knee injury and playing just three times off the bench in the CSL this season.
